/******************************************************************************

                            Question 4: Oxygen Plants 

Write a Java program to calculate the number of plants that can be placed on a floor area and the amount of oxygen produced per day.

The program should:

Read the floor area of the room (length and breadth in meters)

Read the area occupied by a single plant (in cmÂ²)

Calculate the total number of plants that can be placed on the floor
(ignore fractional plants)

Calculate the oxygen produced per day, assuming each plant produces 0.9 litres of oxygen

ðŸ“¤ Output format:

Display the result in the following format:

Total plants placed on floor area <length>*<breadth> is <number_of_plants> plants produces <oxygen> litres of oxygen in a day


*******************************************************************************/
import java.util.*;
public class Main{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        double l = sc.nextDouble();
        double b = sc.nextDouble();
        double f_area=l*b;
        double p_area = sc.nextDouble();
        p_area /=10000;
        double total_plants = f_area/p_area;
        total_plants = total_plants - (total_plants % 1);
        double ox = total_plants * 0.9;
        
        System.out.println("Total plants placed on floor area "
        +f_area+
        " is "
        +(int) total_plants+
        " plants produces "
        +String.format("%.2f",ox)+
        " liters of oxygen in a day");
    }
}
